obo:ECO_0007695  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1847  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 2D: \"Electron microscopy provided further evidence that TNIK is present in dendritic spines and localized both to pre- and postsynaptic compartments, with enrichment in the latter (Figure 2d).\". Experimental description: Rat brains are used for the ultrastructure localization of TNIK at synapses and biochemical fractionation experiments, hippocampal cultures from rats are used for the immunolocalization of TNIK to excitatory synapses.\n\nLiteral from M&M:\n\"Electron microscopy\nAll procedures relating to the care and treatment of animals were in accordance with the institutional and National Institutes of Health guidelines. Pentobarbital- anesthetized (60mgkg-1 intraperitoneal) male Sprague-Dawley rats (3-5 months old, Charles River, Raleigh, NC, USA) were intracardially perfused with heparinized saline followed by 500 ml of fixative.\"\n\"Rat hippocampal and cortical neuronal cultures were prepared from 18-day-old embryonic rats as previously described.37\"\n\"Synaptosome and PSD fractionation of rat brain\nThe fractionation was performed as previously described.24\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1847" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

